-- Zimbabwe’s Bulawayo City Seeks $82m for Water, Newsday Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-12-14T07:54:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-14/zimbabwe-s-bulawayo-city-seeks-82m-for-water-newsday-reports.html
Govt of  Zimbabwe ’s second-largest
city wants money for medium-term plan to restore water supply,
Newsday newspaper reports, citing Mayor Thaba Moyo and Eddie Cross, a Movement for Democratic Change party official.
* City faces a “critical” water shortage, Harare-based
newspaper says on its  website 
* City has already raised $37m, Newsday says
* NOTE: City may cut water supply to once a wk from present 4
days a wk  To contact the reporter on this story:
